2. Preprocessing¶

  • Baseline correction
  • Bandpass filter
  • ICA
In [19]:
# Random sampling from tasks 15 period of 15 seconds to train ICA
sample = {}
np.random.seed(101)

for idx, task in enumerate(tasks):
    _WINDOW = 15
    _min, _max = np.min(task), np.max(task)
        
    for i in range(5):
        start = np.random.randint(_min, _max - _WINDOW)
        sample[f"Task{idx}_{i}"] = {'start': start + DIFF_TIME, 'end': start + DIFF_TIME + _WINDOW}
In [20]:
plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = [20, 5]

for k, v in sample.items():
    sample_raw = raw.copy().crop(v['start'], v['end'])
    
    # Apply baseline correction
    sample_raw_baseline = sample_raw.copy()
    sample_raw_baseline.apply_function(baseline_calc)
    
    # Apply bandpass filter
    sample_raw_bandpass = sample_raw_baseline.copy()
    sample_raw_bandpass.apply_function(butter_bandpass_filter)
    
    # Apply ICA
    sample_raw_train = sample_raw_bandpass.copy()
    sample_raw_corrected = sample_raw_bandpass.copy()
    
    # Train
    ica = ICA(method="extended-infomax", random_state=1)
    ica.fit(sample_raw_train)
    
    # Plot ICA component 
    ica.plot_components(inst=sample_raw_train)
    
    # Excluding channel
    to_exclude = input()
    to_exclude = list(map(int, to_exclude.split()))
    
    ica.exclude = to_exclude
    
    # Apply on entire data
    
    ## Baseline correction
    raw_baseline = raw.copy()
    raw_baseline.apply_function(baseline_calc)
    
    ## Bandpass filter
    raw_bandpass = raw_baseline.copy()
    raw_bandpass.apply_function(butter_bandpass_filter)
    
    ## ICA
    raw_corrected = raw_bandpass.copy()
    ica.apply(raw_corrected)
    
    # Ploting PSD:
    for idx, ch in enumerate(raw_corrected.ch_names):
#         plt.subplot(2,5,idx+1)
        f, pxx = plot_psd(raw_corrected.copy().pick(ch).get_data()[0,:])
        plt.plot(f,pxx, label = 'ch')
        
    plt.title(k)
    plt.show()
